CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 14, 1962, pg. A14 reads: "The Chi's Have Fun - The tables above represent just a few of 25 hosted by the Chi's at the supper dance last Saturday night...Dr. Earl Simms' table in the next photo includes, clockwise: Mrs. Huey Bowe, Mr. Bowe, Mrs. Earl Simms Jr., Earl Simms Jr., Mr. and Mrs. Lester Holmes, Mrs. Andrew Vaughn, Mr. Vaughn and Dr. and Mrs. Earl Simms Sr. Dr. and Mrs. Eugene Youngue's table is in the background."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait, clockwise: Mr. and Mrs. Huey  Bowe, Mr. and Mrs. Earl Simms Jr., Mr. and Mrs. Lester Holmes, Mr. and Mrs. Andrew Vaughn, and Dr. and Mrs. Earl Simms Sr., seated around banquet table in Hilton Hotel for Chi Delta Mu supper dance
